- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper introduces a new language for hybrid computation and discusses its semantics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another likely category because hybrid computation is relevant to control theory and the paper mentions applications in this area. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category because the paper introduces a new monad for hybrid computation and discusses its properties. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible because the paper discusses the difficulties of analyzing and describing emergent behaviors in hybrid computation, which could be related to computational complexity.
